#Text=Since then , Malta 's dependable  shining star " has been Chiara Siracusa , who goes by her first name in her music career .

column1: #Text=First competing in 1998 at the age of 21 , she was pushed to the brink of victory until the votes from the final country that evening leveled her placement to third .

#Text=Her rendition of the song " The One That I Love , " and the recognition she received not only for herself , but for her country , made her a star in Malta overnight , and helped her launch a singing career in Europe .
#Text=She would later return to the Contest in 2005 with " Angel , " an anthem she penned herself , and achieved second place .
#Text=Now , in 2009 , she will be going back to Eurovision for a third try , hoping for the " 3-2-1 " charm and a victory — something that has eluded her thus far .
#Text=Her entry , the ballad " What If We , " has special memories for Chiara ; it is dedicated to her father , who is recently deceased .
#Text=What if Chiara could take home the gold in Moscow ; for Malta , for her father , and for herself ?
#Text=Only time will tell .
#Text=Chiara took time out of her Eurovision promotional schedule to answer some questions from Wikinews ' Mike Halterman about her past performances , and most importantly , her upcoming one .
#Text=This is the fourth in a series of interviews with past Eurovision contestants , which will be published sporadically in the lead-up to mid-May 's next contest in Moscow .
#Text=You 'll be going to Moscow for a third try at possibly winning Eurovision .
#Text=Why did you decide to compete this year ?
#Text=How did your partnership with Marc Paelinck and Gregory Bilsen come about ?
#Text=Well , I met Marc Paelinck long time ago through a friend in Belgium .
#Text=We started working together and it brought us to this collaboration today .
#Text=I was thinking of going back to the festival [ for a long time ] and this year felt like the right year to do so .
#Text=Eurovision fans from across Europe picked you as the wide favorite to win Malta 's preselection this year .
#Text=Were you as confident ?
#Text=Were you nervous about competing in the semi-final rounds this time around , or did you think this was something you could handle ?
